{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}} {{Infobox company | name = InnoGames GmbH | logo = InnoGames GmbH.jpg | type = [[Subsidiary]] | industry = [[Video game industry]] | founded = {{Start date and age|df=yes|2007}} in [[Stade]], Germany | founders = {{Unbulleted list|Eike Klindworth|Hendrik Klindworth|Michael Zillmer}} | hq_location_city = [[Hamburg]] | hq_location_country = [[Germany]] | key_people = {{Unbulleted list|Hendrik Klindworth {{small|([[Chief operating officer|CEO]])}}|Michael Zillmer {{small|([[Chief operating officer|COO]])}}|Christian Pern {{small|([[Chief marketing officer|CMO]])}}|Armin Busen {{small|([[Chief product officer|CPO]])}}}} | num_employees = 420 | num_employees_year = 2018 | parent = [[Modern Times Group]] | divisions = InnoGames Düsseldorf | website = {{URL|innogames.com}} }}
'''InnoGames GmbH''' is a German [[video game developer]] based in [[Hamburg]]. Founded in 2007, it focuses on the development of [[Browser game|browser]] and [[mobile game]]s. The company now has more than 200 million registered players and by 2017, it reached a revenue of {{Euro|161.5&nbsp;million|link=yes}}.<ref>{{citation|title=InnoGames reports revenue growth of 24% last year, up to €161.5m|date=20 February 2018|url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2018-02-20-innogames-reports-revenue-growth-of-24-percent-up-to-161-5m|publisher=[[gamesindustry.biz]]}}</ref>
==History== In 2003, founders Eike and Hendrik Klindworth created and released the browser-based online game ''[[Tribal Wars]]'' as a hobby project. At the end of 2005, the game reached more than 50,000 active players and today has a total of 55 million registered players.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://2p.com/34601305_1/Tribal-Wars-2-Launched-on-iOS-Features-Real-time-And-Strategic-Battles-Online-by-crazy-guy.htm |title=Tribal Wars 2 Launched on iOS, Seamlessly Sharing Data With Android and Browser |last= |first= |date=24 June 2015 |website=2p.com|access-date=}}</ref> Due to the success, the three founders decided to work full-time on the development and publishing of browser games. Then in early 2007, InnoGames was founded to handle the operation and continued development of the [[TribalWars|Die Stämme]] (English name Tribal Wars). Since then, the company has developed new games and publishes their games worldwide.<ref name=":1">{{citation |title=History: Innogames. |date=28 Aug 2012 |url=http://corporate.innogames.com/en/history.html |publisher=InnoGames |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130813073954/http://corporate.innogames.com/en/history.html |archivedate=13 August 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
The company released its second game, The West, in 2008. That same year InnoGames moved to Hamburg-Harburg and hired additional employees.<ref name=":1" /> As the company continued to grow, they released their third game, Grepolis, on 2009. Since 2013, Grepolis is playable as an app for iOS and Android devices.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://gamecry.com/blog/grepolis-app-iphone/ |title=Grepolis App Now Available on iPhone |last= |first= |date=4 September 2013 |work=GameCry.com|access-date=}}</ref> Its first city-builder, Forge of Empires, was published in 2012. The game includes a journey through time that begins in the Stone Age and guides the player through the ages of human history. As of late-July, 2018, the latest era is the Virtual Future, but further extensions are planned. Forge of Empires was awarded the German Computer Game Prize in 2013 as the best browser game.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://de.mmooftheyear.com/hall-of-fame |title=MMO of the Year Hall of Fame |last= |first= |date= |website=MMO of the Year|access-date=4 May 2017}}</ref> Since 5 June 2014 the game is also playable as an app on the iPad.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.adweek.com/digital/innogames-brings-forge-of-empires-to-ipad/ |title=InnoGames brings Forge of Empires to iPad |last=Shaul |first=Brandy |date=5 June 2014 |work=ADWEEK|access-date=4 May 2017}}</ref> The iPhone version followed on September 2014 <ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.technologytell.com/apple/141070/forge-empires-now-available-iphone/ |title=Forge of Empires now optimized for iPhone |last=Marceau |first=Erica |date=29 September 2014 |work=Technology Tell|access-date=4 May 2017}}</ref> and the Android version on 25 March 2015.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://blog.forgeofempires.com/?p=1063 |title=Forge of Empires Comes to Android |last= |first= |date=25 March 2015 |website=Forge of Empires Blog|access-date=4 May 2017}}</ref> Following Forge of Empires' Android version in 2015, the German developer published its second city-building MMO, Elvenar in April<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://mmos.com/review/elvenar |title=Elvenar Overview |last= |first= |date= |website=MMOs.com|access-date=4 May 2017}}</ref>
===Further growth=== In May 2010, the investor Fidelity Growth Partners Europe (FGPE) joined InnoGames with a minority share. Also in 2010, former [[Electronic Arts]] executive Gerhard Florin joined InnoGames as Chairman.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2011-02-02-florin-takes-chairman-role-at-innogames |title=Florin takes chairman role at InnoGames |author=Matt Martin |publisher=GamesIndustry.biz |date=2 February 2011}}</ref> By 2016, MTG (Modern Times Group) acquired 35% of the German free-to-play developer.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |url=http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2016-10-13-mtg-acquires-35-percent-of-innogames-for-90-million |title=MTG acquires 35% of InnoGames for €90 million |last=Handrahan |first=Matthew |date=13 Oct 2016 |website=gamesindustry.biz|access-date=}}</ref> 2016 was also InnoGames' most successful year, having a 68% year-on-year growth.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.develop-online.net/news/innogames-post-record-financials-after-a-decade-of-year-on-year-growth/0229292 |title=Players managed 600m hours of gameplay on InnoGames titles in 2016 |last=Tucker |first=Jake |date=7 Feb 2017 |website=Develop|access-date=}}</ref> The following year, InnoGames acquired Wooga's strategy game Warlords, promising a relaunch of the game.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://venturebeat.com/2017/02/23/innogames-acquires-woogas-strategy-game-warlords/ |title=InnoGames acquires Wooga's stratgy game Warlords |last=Takahashi |first=Dean |date=23 February 2017 |work=VentureBeat|access-date=4 May 2017}}</ref> Later, on 2 May 2017 the Swedish Company MTG increased its stake in InnoGames by buying 51% of the company <ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.mmobomb.com/news/swedish-entertainment-company-buys-51-stake-innogames/ |title=Swedish Entertainment Company Buys 51% Stake in InnoGames |last=Winter |first=Jason |date=2 May 2017 |work=|access-date=4 May 2017}}</ref>
==Mobile initiative== The first title that the company launched on mobile platforms was Tribal Wars, its founding game. ''Grepolis'', another of its strategy browser titles, was also launched onto mobile platforms in 2013.<ref>{{citation |title=E3 – InnoGames' Growth & The Move to Fully Cross-Platform Experiences.Two of six games have a mobile app. |publisher=RTSGURU |date=26 June 2013 |url=http://www.rtsguru.com/article/6090/E3-InnoGames-Growth-The-Move-to-Fully-Cross-Platform-Experiences.html}}</ref> Finally in 2014, [[Forge of Empires]] was also converted to tablet and mobile <ref>us.forgeofempires.com</ref> and increased the company's revenues. InnoGames managed to transition from browser to mobile, even as other studios have faltered. The company now has four studios which develop and maintain their strategy games.<ref name=":0" /> Despite focusing on mobile, their CEO has said that the company will continue developing and maintaining browser games in the future <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.f2p.com/interview-with-hendrik-klindworth-ceo-of-innogames/ |title=Interview with Hendrik Klindworth, CEO of InnoGames |last= |first= |date=10 Oct 2015 |website=F2P.com|access-date=}}</ref>
